                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Now `cv1`-`cv6` are initialized with real objects instead of `null`. Alpine can safely evaluate `cv1.bg_colour` etc. before `init()` runs.\n\nThe fix: `cv1` through `cv6` were initialized as `null` in the Alpine data object. Alpine evaluates reactive bindings like `:style=\"'background:var('+cv1.bg_colour+')'...\"` synchronously when the component mounts, before `x-init` (which sets them to real objects via `_cvDefaults()`). Accessing `.bg_colour` on `null` throws a TypeError, which Alpine reports as \"cv1 is not defined\", cascading to every binding in the component failing.\n\nThe fix initializes all six with the same default shape inline in the object literal, so they're valid objects from the moment Alpine first evaluates any binding."
                  }
                ],
