                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "## SUMMARY\n\n**Root Cause**: When `v1`, `v2`, `v3` were initialized as `null` in the return object, Alpine's getter for `av` (`get av() { return this['v' + this.activeVariant]; }`) would return `null` before `init()` ran. When Alpine tried to evaluate expressions like `av.hero_overline` during component mount (before `x-init` executes), it accessed properties on `null`, causing errors.\n\n**Fix Applied**: Changed `v1: null, v2: null, v3: null` to `v1: {}, v2: {}, v3: {}` and used `Object.assign()` in `init()` to populate them instead of direct assignment. This ensures `av` always returns an object (even if empty initially), preventing null reference errors during Alpine's synchronous binding evaluation.\n\nThe page should now load without Alpine errors."
